Former Premier League stars, Peter Schmeichel, Jamie Carragher and Thierry Henry, have predicted the team to win this season’s Champions League trophy. Recall that Chelsea won the Champions League last season after beating Manchester City 1-0 in the final. The likes of Chelsea, Real Madrid, Atletico Madrid, Bayern Munich, Liverpool, Benfica, Villarreal and Manchester City are currently in the Champions League quarter-final. Liverpool defeated Benfica 3-1 in the Champions League first-leg tie on Tuesday, while Man City won Atletico Madrid 1-0. Chelsea will face Real Madrid in the Champions League first leg on Wednesday night and Bayern Munich will tackle Villarreal. The winner of this season’s Champions League will be crowned on May 28. Providing their predictions for CBS Sports: Schmeichel picked ‘Bayern Munich’ to win the Champions League. On his part, Carragher backed ‘Liverpool’ to win the Champions League. Henry, meanwhile, tipped ‘Manchester City.’